RULE 65(b)(1)(B) CERTIFICATION OF NOTICE EFFORTS

I, [Your Name], certify as follows:

1. Efforts to Give Notice. On August 24, 2025 at 09:15 and 14:30, I emailed and called counsel for Defendant ([email@firm.com], (555) 555â€‘5555) regarding Plaintiffâ€™s intended TRO filing. I left voicemail messages and requested a sameâ€‘day meetâ€‘andâ€‘confer. I received no response. I also sent a copy of the TRO package via email to [secondary contact] at 18:05.

2. Why Notice Should Not Be Required. Immediate and irreparable harm will occur before an adversarial hearing can be held: Defendant plans to [imminent action] within 24 hours, which would cause nonâ€‘compensable injury to Plaintiffâ€™s constitutional rights and professional standing. Providing additional notice risks precipitating the very harm sought to be prevented.

3. Attachments. Exhibits include email timestamps (Ex. A), call logs (Ex. B), and a sworn declaration detailing urgency (Ex. C).

I declare under penalty of perjury that the foregoing is true and correct. 28 U.S.C. Â§ 1746.

